<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-878-320  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 878 320.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  Nov 13 1989 v11 n46 p116(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>How we tested and scored Micro Channel Architecture computers.andO;(benchmarking methods)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Kvitka, Andre; Wong, Eugene J.; Smith, Gregory S.; Black, Lauren;Sommer, Daniel; Miller, Michael J.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The procedures used for testing and scoring twelve Micro ChannelArchitecture microcomputers for performance, setup,serviceability, and support are described.andP;  Performance categoriesinclude speed in both memory-intensive and disk-intensiveapplications; software compatibility; hardware compatibility; andexpandability.andP;  Compatibility tests include Crosstalk XVI 3.61;Lotus 1-2-3 2.2 and 3.0; Desqview 2.25; Microsoft Word underDesqview; and such hardware as a Hayes Smartmodem 2400P and an IBMPS/2 Display Adapter.andP;  Documentation should explain how to set upand use the system, include accurate illustrations, an index,troubleshooting help, and hardware customization information.andP;  Thesetup category includes ease of use; serviceability is dividedinto design, support policies, and technical support.andP;  Valuescores are obtained by weighing price against performance.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Performance MeasurementTestingComparisonSpecificationsRatings.andO;Feature:   illustrationgraph.andO;Caption:   Speed tests, memory-intensive programs. (graph)Speed tests, disk-intensive programs. (graph)MCA computers. (graph)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>